    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>More Harry Potter!</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Susannah Hendrey, who is 9, says she is happy that newest Harry Potter book is 600 pages long</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I disagree with a May 23 letter about the new Harry Potter book. I think it's great that the book will be 600 pages long, twice the usual length.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I disagree with a May 23 letter about the new Harry Potter book. I think it's great that the book will be 600 pages long, twice the usual length.</p>
        <p>Lots of children who don't normally read have been drawn into books by the first three Potter books. They'll want to know the rest of the story, so they'll read all 600 pages.</p>
        <p>Then they'll realize that a long book doesn't seem so long when it's good. Maybe when they realize this, they'll read more long books.</p>
        <p>And I'm especially happy because I love reading (I'm 9 years old) and I'm a big fan of the Harry Potter books. The longer the better!</p>
        <p>SUSANNAH HENDREY  Shoreham, N.Y., May 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
